@stevenlix @ybrnathan FYI

would it be possible to run with execution trace?
in python, enable_profiling like this example: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/test/python/onnxruntime_test_python.py#L408

the profile file should show the nodes executed and which ones assigned to TensorRT , CUDA, CPU etc.

TensorRT doesn't support all the ops in mask rcnn, and we haven't finished implementing all the cuda kernels, so most likely some nodes are executing on CPU , resulting in the slow performance.
the profile trace would confirm it.

Yes, some of them runs on CPU

Hoping for your guys implement op such as `Gather` `Concate`  `Suqeeze` `Transpose` etc in CUDA or TensorRT.

FYI, all ops used inside maskrcnn.onnx were:

```
Unsqueeze,Constant,Conv,Mul,Add,Relu,MaxPool,Shape,Gather,Concat,Cast,Slice,Div,Resize,ConstantOfShape,NonZero,Transpose,Reshape,Expand,Sigmoid,ReduceMin,TopK,Squeeze,Sub,Clip,Exp,Split,Less,Not,And,NonMaxSuppression,Sqrt,Log,Floor,Equal,RoiAlign,Scatter,Gemm,Softmax,Flatten,Greater,ConvTranspose

```

yes, it is work in progress. for example there are PR's for CUDA TopK and NonZero open currently,
specifically for making MaskRCNN, FastRCNN models faster.
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/2056
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/1919
@jinfagang Do you see ops running on TensorRT in the profile trace? If the model is available, I can check from TRT side.

@stevenlix  It's many many ops, it can see only some of them running in tensorrt. For your inference, I post all json log here:

```
{"cat" : "Node","pid" :6137,"tid" :6137,"dur" :686,"ts" :10515726,"ph" : "X","name" :"Memcpy_755_kernel_time","args" : {"provider" : "TensorrtExecutionProvider","op_name" : "MemcpyToHost"}},
```

OH, I found all tensorrt providers runs only on op called `MemcpyFromHost`.....

Mask-RCNN and Fast-RCNN GPU performance optimization is in progress, we tested its performance in private branch, it can achieve ~126ms on 1080-Ti GPU. Many of those Ops are pending in PR, will be merged shortly.
@ybrnathan  That sound promising! BTW, I think pytorch native CUDA runs MaskRCNN+Resnet50+FPN can achieves 16fps on GTX180ti or so.
Does there a time for it?
same problem. maybe the optimization in tensorrt consume the time?
